Depth — distance from root TO node (top down)
Height — distance from node TO leaf (bottom up)
For the whole tree: max depth == max height, same value, different perspectives
Remember that: Leaf nodes have zero height

1. Max Depth — Number of Nodes
public int maxDepth_Nodes(TreeNode root) {
    if (root == null) return 0;
    int left = maxDepth_Nodes(root.left);
    int right = maxDepth_Nodes(root.right);
    return Math.max(left, right) + 1;  // +1 counts current node
}

2. Max Depth — Number of Edges
public int maxDepth_Edges(TreeNode root) {
    if (root == null) return -1;  // -1 because root has 0 edges above it
    int left = maxDepth_Edges(root.left);
    int right = maxDepth_Edges(root.right);
    return Math.max(left, right) + 1;
}

